<br>
1st post: I like the group of people I play with and got a little mad at things that were happening around me. I decided to write a rant about it. I got some positive and negative feedback out of it (both of which I really wanted to see <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ). Maybe did a little spring cleaning... I will explain a little later.<br>
<br>
2nd post: Just to clarify, for any one who wasn't there, I blew up UNNECESSARILY when I thought my post was deleted. Just to let you know.... It wasn't deleted <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
3rd post: This one. Several people came up to me and asked me to rejoin, or just assumed I would rejoin because of how silly the 2nd post and my unneeded blow up was. I am some what stubborn in my ways and was going to stay out of any guild for a long time, until a long discussion with my good friends (in game and in real life) Tormark and Xzanthos. <br>
<br>
Playing with a group of people in real life changes the aspect of this entire game. Its no longer a place you can come to and play a game. It turns into another place that you hang out with your friends. Now if something goes wrong in game and it was one of my RL friends that did it or were a part of it I can yell at them or vise versa they can yell at me about it.<br>
<br>
Well I had a real long discussion about this. A lot of things had changed in the short (shoooooorrrrtttt) period of time that I had been away. Like the proverbial spring cleaning on the &quot;City of Pax Familla&quot; &quot;Town drunks and whinos...&quot; Some what started by the rant that I had with my first post and other posts that I don't really need to talk about cause you know what they are, if you are an avid reader of this board.<br>
<br>
We talked about ( Tormark, Xzanthos and I) things that had happened and how many people other than my self that had similar feelings about these same problems. It all came down to the fact that there were a lot of people in pax who felt the same way I did but 1.. didn't want to leave pax because they loved it so much, 2.. have chosen alternate paths to show their discomfort with the problems that are facing pax. A point was brought up that I wouldn't still post on this board or hang out with people in pax if I really didn't want to rejoin.<br>
<br>
There were a couple things I wanted to say before my next question.<br>
1. My post was not DELETED, that was my fault and this boards fault for having a poor display scheme.<br>
2. I don't care who said it. &quot;Its not what PAX FAMILLA can do for you, its what you can do for pax&quot; Look 95% of people who say that are blowing smoke out or up something and are just saying that because they don't do any thing themselves. The 5% of people that should say that, because they have done things for pax, Don't say any thing.<br>
3. Pax is not a DEMOCRACY and is not a DICTATORSHIP If you want to join a dictatorship go get hired at Sony. For a democracy.......Its a game, need I say more.<br>
4. Finally any undo hate thus directed at Blancalupa coming from my posts or caused by my posts or others should be stricken from the records. I at a previous time was a guild leader or member of a ruling body. Trust me its more work than should ever be associated with a game. But I would do it again. And if I rejoin or not... Blanca if you need a body guard, I'm only a cleric but I would be happy to assist you. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Its a game. One highly addictive, life entangling, emotion heated........ game. Pretty funny when you think about it. Hehe.<br>
<br>
Finally, here is the question. Do you want me back? I'm not crawling on my hands and knees. I'm posing this question because I want to come back and because I have been asked by several people. If there are people in pax who would prefer I not come back so be it. I'm not going to make half the people happy and half mad. <br>
<br>
Or just sit back and....<br>
